CONDITIONAL STATEMENTS:--
 *used to decide whether code has to be executed or skipped based on condition.
 *To make the set of instructions(block of code)(conditional block) execute only when the given condition is true.
 *Execute in a seq (line-by-line)
 
Block of code:- 
*Set of instructions
*it will execute only when the specific condition is true

Condition:- 
*An expression that evaluates a result(True or False)
*Ex:-console.log(5>6)

There are 5 METHODS to write conditional statements.
--if
--if -else
--else if
--switch
-terinary operator

1."IF":--
 *only one possible condition.
 *If given condition is True it will execute otherwise it will be skipped.
 **Syntax:- 
           if(condition){
            --block of code
           }
 **Example:-
    INPUT:-
	<script>
        let a=5
        let b=6
        if(a<b){
            document.write("Hello World")
        }
	document.write("Brilliant Veena")
	</script>
   OUTPUT:-
	   Hello World
	   Brilliant Veena


2."ELSE":--
  **Example:-
   *INPUT:- <script>
        let a=5
        let b=6
        if(a>b){
            document.write("Hello World","<br>")
        }
        else{
             document.write("hi Lucky","<br>")
        }
        document.write("brilliant Veena")
        </script>
  *OUTPUT:-
          hi lucky
          brilliant veena


3."ELSE IF":--
 **EXAMPLE 1:-
   INPUT:- <script>
        let age=prompt("Enter your age?")
        let name=prompt("enter your name?")
        if(age<18){
            alert(name+"you are too young to marry")
        }
        else if(age>35){
            alert(name+"you are too old to marry")
        }
        else{
            alert(name+"perfect age to marry")
        }
        </script>
   **OUTPUT:- 
	   Veena perfect age to marry

**EXAMPLE 2:-
 INPUT:- <script>
        let a=prompt("Enter a score: ")
        let b=prompt("Enter b score: ")
        let c=a+b
        if((a>300 || b>300) && (c<500)){
                alert("valid to team up")
        }
        else{
            alert("not valid to team up")
        }
        </script>
	      
 OUTPUT:-      
	not valid to team up
           
